SIMPLE: quilting
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quilting
<hw>Quilt"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of stitching
or running in patterns, as in making a quilt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A quilting bee. See <er>Bee</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The material used for making quilts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A coating of strands of rope for
a water vessel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quin</ent>⟦br⟧
